tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Laboratory results are largely within normal limits. Mildly decreased hemoglobin suggests borderline anemia, which may warrant clinical correlation, especially given the patient"s age. Platelet distribution width is elevated, possibly indicating increased platelet size variability, but platelet count is normal. No evidence of renal dysfunction, electrolyte imbalance, or abnormal glucose metabolism. Overall, no acute laboratory abnormalities detected.
